details.description:
A Cause for Tea is a collaborative fundraising effort for New Life Nicaragua, HELP Pregnancy Resource Center, and other non-profit organizations that work to meet the needs of and empower women and children.
We are a close-knit team of humanitarians and artists working with local leaders, community members, and non-profit organizations to train and advocate for women and children, develop them for successful and influential integration into their communities with a vision for self-empowerment in order to escape poverty and to bring relief to suffering from malnutrition, lack of shelter, clothing, and education.

reviews_data.review_text: It's just delicious and the house is beautiful, almost as if we went back in time...❤️❤️❤️

Exceptional! I felt as if I was invited in with THE BEST Southern hospitality. Everything is charming and cheerful! I couldn't help but look in awe of the beauty of the house and the joy of those working there. .... then our food came out. Wow. Everything was delicious. We had the tea sandwiches, scones (savory biscuits... scones are dry and these were anything but dry), Chicken on a Holiday, Chicken salad, fruit, and of course we had tea. We were too full to try more... but im happy to report the brownie, lemon bar, and slice of lemon cake were taken to-go and were amazing. I'm still dreaming of the lemon cake! ❤️❤️❤️ A Cause For Tea and the team did not disappoint! Brovo!
We did the tea experience upstairs and it was so much fun!  The tea was really good and the food was as well.  I highly recommend!
First visit here was amazing! The food was hot and the tea was splendid. Our server was very helpful and patient when we couldn’t decide what to order! Highly recommend and can’t wait to return!

This place is absolutely fabulous and charming! I had a chicken pot pie, which is well presented and it was OK, but not what I was expecting and I don’t think I would order it again!
But the tea, our waitress for a party of six an atmosphere was just absolutely phenomenal!
I’ll definitely be going back!

Today I celebrate a very special waitress for her exuberance and graciousness. Her name is Katy, and she is officially my new "favorite" waitress at A Cause For Tea!!!
I visited yesterday, 8.15.25, with 2 of my neighbors and we had to wait 45 minutes to be seated and served--that's a long time, but Katy made the  wait worth it! Her kindness is so genuine, she makes the food taste even better.
Thanks and blessings to you, Katy!!!
Lovely and cozy spot to enjoy a wide variety of delicious tea and pastries

I wish there were more than 5 stars.  I took my granddaughter there today for brunch before she leaves for her freshman year of college.  It was purely magical.  From driving into the parking lot with the beautiful gardens…..walking in and getting seated immediately……the decor was amazing.  I’ve read a number of reviews that call it cute.  Cute is not the correct description.  It is elegant.   Beautifully appointed with antique furnishings.  The lighting and art are to perfection.  The tastefully painted rooms….corals, greens and blues…..everywhere you look!  The menu was vast and something for everyone.  I had the seasonal salad with chicken salad and tomato chicken soup.  The blueberry tea was a perfect choice.  I could go on and on but I encourage you to experience a Cause for Tea yourself.  You will not be disappointed. Not to mention “the cause”……
Very cute place, everything delicious.

A happy marriage between southern and European food and tea.
Amazing people, really great service. Beautiful atmosphere, adorable gift shop.
The food was delicious, the tea was great after I explained how exactly I like my tea, they made it happen.
I took  1 star away because I had to put my purse on the floor when I used the bathroom. There's no hook on the door for bags and coats. And the pastry options was very small, only had 2 types of cakes. American style and a bunch of southern treats I didn't care for. I was really hoping for more English/French/Italian pastry and meal options. I tried the macarons. Absolutely delicious, but it's one tiny puny little cookie for what I consider too much for my pocket. The stars were also very delicious, but it was mostly cream inside and fluffy like whip cream, $8 was very steep for a small tart. I know it's for a good cause but because of how high the prices are, I won't be able to be a regular customer. I'll have to treat myself once in a while.
Also, i'd take another star off for them not having basic drip coffee for non tea drinkers, but I like the place too much to give it a lower rating overall. I invited my friend to come to breakfast with me and she  didn't want to come because she doesn't drink tea. She drinks coffee. Please add a basic drip coffee to your menu. I know it's a lot to deal with finding good beans but it's not an impossible ask because I've seen the gift shop and the loose leaf tea options. So if you can find all those hard to find products, I think you can find a decent vendor for regular drip coffee.
They are a non profit organization who helps many people in need so it really is a cause, not just a brunch place, they raise money to help people.
Cutest tea place ever! The scones were absolutely my favorite—fresh and delicious. The prices were reasonable, and overall I just really enjoyed my time here. Such a lovely spot!
Love the ambiance, service and food!
Had a very nice time here. Went with a group of 8 and we all enjoyed the experience. Such a cute spot with lots of charm. The tea was quite good and the food as well.
Delightful! So many choices. Friendly staff.
Wonderful service,  food was amazing, tea i had was wonderful (cream earl grey).
Excellent!  Cannot wait to go back!

This was a special experience with my daughter and granddaughter.  It’s beautiful inside complete with a gift shop!The array of tea choices, hot or cold with 5 different choices to have it made.  Delicious choices of soup, salads, main courses and deserts is amazing!  We are going back next week!
Excellent service along with incredibly tasty teas and food. We drove 40 minutes for the experience, and it was definitely worth it-- would 10/10 recommend.
Exceptional service, ambience and food menu
Sooo lovely and yummy.

First time here at tea shop in Monroe, NC. 1st pic is tea sandwiches with a pot of tea for $18 USD. 2nd pic is scones, clotted cream and jam with pot of tea for $18 USD. 3rd pic is cheese board with 3 different cheeses and crackers for $22 USD. Was so crowded we had to go up to second floor. Service excellent, food perfect. Highly recommend!

I love all of the fun treats tea and goodies here I’ve applied to work here because I want to be a server but if you go here get the last mango in Paris tea sunny it’s amazing and sooo addicting then to go with it you’re gonna want to get the blissful beef pie which in my opinion is the best thing to eat because it has a base of amazingly delicious mashed potatoes with the sweet beef that is so tender that it melts in your mouth and tastes like it’s been marinating for days and to top it all of it has a buttery flaky and soft puff pastry on top

Great cute place for tea, scones, breakfast and lunch foods with great service in a cute and lovely house !!!
Very cute but needs AC! I felt like I was overheating!

We came in for afternoon tea and ordered scones, which were large and very hard. They didn’t offer Devonshire cream or clotted cream, which was very disappointing—there’s hardly a point in eating a scone without real cream. The server mentioned she accidentally rang me up for an extra scone and asked if I wanted it. I accepted it before realizing they weren’t any good.

We also ordered tea sandwiches, which were cold and soggy—I couldn’t eat them. However, the beef pie, cinnamon toast, and tea were very good. The place was decorated quite nicely.

I drove from Columbia to dine here, and unfortunately, I was disappointed. I wouldn’t return.

Besides the fact that the cause is just, the food is fabulous. I had the chicken salad croissant. Super delicious and not some dainty portion either. I am not a tea aficionado, but everyone in my party thought the tea was special.
A Cause for Tea is a wonderful tea room to enjoy with your girlfriends or family. The food and teas were delicious. They also have a lovely giftshop to browse in after you've eaten.
This is the greatest place for homemade meals. The desserts are wonderful,  the atmosphere is amazing and the staff is so nice.

My loved ones and I absolutely adore A Cause for Tea. The food is delicious, the tea is amazing, the ambiance is so special, and the servers are the best. I just feel happy going there, and I highly recommend it for a special occasion or just a casual drop in.
Love this place!  We have been multiple times,  and love everything we ever had!  Great gifts available for purchase in the gift shop as well. 💗

What a delicious place with a mission and vision that is absolutely amazing! The partner with a Nicaraguan mission to help build homes and support women in Nicaragua, and the support two local Monroe organizations. The whole staffs passion and love for others shows through everything they do. It’s amazing to see them at work and the environment is absolutely everything. I think it’s so important when you go here that you remember they are on mission and you step into that mission when you are there. A kind heart, kind words, and kind attitude are what you should bring with you when you visit. Enjoy the food, have a high-tea party, exclusive events, and enjoy their shop with amazing teas, books, and everything in between for purchase. But keep the coffee at home, this is a Tea House. No, this is THE TEA HOUSE.
I remember when this was the YWAM base for Charlotte! Love the old home. The renovations are wonderful. The food is great!! Also, love the ministry cause.

My new favorite Afternoon Tea spot! Friends and I decided to visit this tea spot after hearing positive reviews. We learned that it's both a reservation and a walk-in spot. You can walk in anytime from 9 am-5 pm for afternoon tea or buy tickets online to reserve and secure a table and enjoy tea with tea sandwiches and pastries all included. If you do the walk-in, you do order a la carte but they do have teapot packages. I got the pot of tea with an assortment of sandwiches. They were delicious and big! I thought they would be cut up into small pieces like other tea houses do but no, these were normal big portions and I was full after eating half a sandwich with tea. Their scones were also very delicious and huge! Very warm and paired well with the butter. I got the spring berry tea and it was exactly what I wanted. Fruity and delicious. No need to add sugar or milk. The ambiance was everything. Antique furniture, cups, napkins just everything was very darling! They have seating upstairs, downstairs, and even outside in their courtyard and porch area. I feel like this is a much better, cheaper option than the Ballantyne tea in the Ballantyne Hotel. The ambiance is much better and you can't beat the prices for sure! They have a little tea shop inside and I bought myself a can of the Spring Berry tea I had with a strainer. I've had plenty of cups at home and it's been delicious! They have a variety of soaps, clothing, accessories teas, honey, etc. You can dress up and even dress down. This is a casual place also. If you are in the mood for a pot of tea you can just swing by and relax. No rush at all. Definitely a favorite and will be back for sure this summer.
Great experience! Absolutely lovely.
A Cause for Tea is always a fun treat for my guests and me. Their food is always good and teas are the top choice. I trust this unique eatery to deliver the goods!

I love the aesthetic of the house. The tea and food is amazing! Prices are fairly reasonable and I finally got my tea pot that I’ve been wanting for a long time!! I also love what this establishment stands for and love how it is helping women and young girls!
Wonderful place for tea and excellent baked goods. Need to offer coffee / specialty coffees.

Very cozy place. I love it. The staff is amazing.
Highly recommend it!!!!

Delightful!!!! Such a lovely place and so thankful to have the tea house in Monroe. It is the most beautiful experience and best place for quality time with ladies. Always such a treat and just love Cause for Tea so, so much!

I brought my mom here for her birthday on 4/19/25. We arrived around 10am and were seated immediately. I saw previous reviews about having to stand in line to order, but they are now full service! Our waitress, Lea was amazing and attentive! The tea was delicious, all of our food was amazing and fresh. The baked brie...🤤 Lea brought a platter of desserts out to us while we were eating so we could preview without having to get up. She even put a candle on the brownie we got as a personal touch for my mom's birthday! We will definitely be back and will be bringing friends with us!

I’ve made many visits to A Cause for Tea and never have been disappointed. Such a pleasant staff and delicious selections from extensive menu. The gift shop has something for everyone. The decor is simply charming.If you want a very happy experience, go to A Cause for Tea.

We all want to find a little less busy time to go back again. They had a couple rooms devoted to really cute gift shop items as well. Super charming inside. Everyone loved it!

Arrived at about 9; 30 on a rainy Saturday morning and the place was packed.  They offer a full menu of tea with the description of each. They also have a lovely brunch menu on the weekends, plus a shorter menu during the week.  I enjoyed a cherry almond tea with a chicken and waffle dish plus a blueberry scone.  I usually always get the chicken salad which is fabulous. However, since we went so early in the morning I wanted more of a breakfast item.

Absolutely love A Cause for Tea and recommend for all tea lovers. They have wonderful meals, snacks, and accommodations for kiddos (who don’t like tea). Can’t say enough good things about this place. On rotation for me and my girlfriends.

What a beautiful house! Allie took good care of us and was very nice.  The Provence tea was delicious, the presentation of everything was great, and the sandwiches were perfect with the tea. Hughly recommend!

Love this place. It’s truly one of a kind, that takes you back in time. I’ve brought so many friends and guests here. And everyone enjoys it. She recommended the soup so I decided to try it. One of the best french onion soups I’ve had. I got the foggy chai to drink and it was DELICIOUS!

The place is cute and worth a visit, so I’m giving it 3 stars.
However, we waited 3 hours (party of 3 + 1 infant), and despite trying to call ahead to check the wait time, no one answered. Since we had driven 50 minutes for the experience, we decided to wait. The boutique was charming and well-decorated, which helped pass the time.

When we finally got a table, we ordered the baked Brie we’d been looking forward to, only to be told they were out (at 2 PM on a Saturday). Disappointing. The macaron was dry and too cold, the brownie was also dry, but the pecan bar was decent.

Overall, it was a disappointing experience, and we won’t return.

reviews_data.review_text: I had a wonderful first experience at A Cause for Tea.  We had the Perfect Combination of a sweets plate with a pot of Peaches and Cream tea.  I had the chicken salad croissant (large portion) and my daughter had the Charming Chicken Pie.  Every single thing was delicious.  The service was great and the entire staff so nice.

The ordering process was a counter style setup that was a bit confusing due to the time of day and rather limited space slotted to the area.

I ordered "tea and scones" a fairly common order for a "tea room".  The scones were quite large and rather bland in flavor.

I was expecting a small pot of tea but received a large "soup cup" of tea with two tea bags in the cup.

Once the food was delivered we did not see a waitress for the rest of the meal. I ended up never getting the refill of hot water I wanted and after 20 or so minutes was able to chase down an attendant to obtain a box to take one of my scones home.

Overall a very nice place that could be a real gem if managed properly.
Rushed us not could have been more friendly considering the prices!
Really well run tea house with ample parking. The atmosphere is southern and adorable. The food is fresh and scrumptious. We can’t wait to go back!
This establishment is truly great.My wife and I went there for lunch and it was really good.Located in a beautiful historical home the atmosphere is exceptional along with service.Monroe has a gem!

1st time there. The place was beautiful. Atmosphere was nice, calm, we could have sat on the porch all afternoon. The house, the vintage China, using vintage handkerchiefs as napkins. The food and desserts were really good. The chicken pot pie was amazing. I had 2 teas, iced chai and a cup of hot earl gray, both very good.The staff was really friendly. The chocolate cake and the lemon tart were both delicious. They were quick to response and replaced the piece of cake I had, since there were egg shells in the cake. We will definitely be back since we already know what we are going to order. The only thing is that I  wished the staff came to the table to take our orders. The room where you have to go to order your food is very small  and when you exit the room you go right into a dining room and when it is crowded it hard to maneuver around. Also, it is better to order and dessert all at one time.

If you're seeking a spot where dessert dreams come true and tea time is elevated to an art form, look no further than Decadent Desserts and Tasty Tea. Nestled in the heart of the city, this charming establishment offers a delightful escape for those with a sweet tooth and an appreciation for fine tea.

The dessert menu is nothing short of extraordinary. From rich, velvety chocolate mousse to perfectly flaky pastries, every item is a testament to the chef's expertise and passion. The standout, however, is the triple-layered caramel cake—a heavenly combination of buttery layers and luscious caramel that melts in your mouth.

Complementing these indulgent treats is a carefully curated tea selection. Each blend is chosen for its unique flavor profile and quality, providing a perfect pairing for the desserts. Overall, it was a disappointing experience, and we won’t return.

If you're seeking a spot where dessert dreams come true and tea time is elevated to an art form, look no further than Decadent Desserts and Tasty Tea. Nestled in the heart of the city, this charming establishment offers a delightful escape for those with a sweet tooth and an appreciation for fine tea.

The dessert menu is nothing short of extraordinary. From rich, velvety chocolate mousse to perfectly flaky pastries, every item is a testament to the chef's expertise and passion. The standout, however, is the triple-layered caramel cake—a heavenly combination of buttery layers and luscious caramel that melts in your mouth.

Complementing these indulgent treats is a carefully curated tea selection. Each blend is chosen for its unique flavor profile and quality, providing a perfect pairing for the desserts. The Earl Grey is a classic, with a fragrant hint of bergamot, while the jasmine tea offers a delicate floral note that enhances the sweetness of the pastries.

The ambiance of Decadent Desserts and Tasty Tea adds to the overall experience. The elegant décor and soothing background music create a relaxed atmosphere, ideal for enjoying a leisurely afternoon. The staff is attentive and knowledgeable, offering excellent recommendations based on your preferences.

In summary, Decadent Desserts and Tasty Tea is a must-visit for dessert aficionados and tea enthusiasts alike. With its exquisite offerings and inviting atmosphere, it's a place where every visit feels like a special occasion.

From the onset, we were confused about the ordering process as we expected to be seated & to have a server come to take our order in the usual order. However, we were ushered down a narrow hallway to a delicatessen-styled room where we were handed menus & instructed to place our orders with the clerk. After doing so, and paying, we were handed a table number card and instructed to wander about and find an available table. We were starting to feel as though we were in an overly decorated-Starbucks and not tea establishment at all.
Once we found an available table, it took some time for our food to arrive. Our scones & pots arrived first and we asked our waiter for the steeping time & a saucer to remove & dispose the tea bags. He looked at us completely confused but did wander off to find a saucer, but was baffled over our initial question.
Next we received the sandwiches which were an overall disappointment. They were nothing special and very bland.
The scones were massive but were hard, dry, and crunchy! Crunchy scones! They did come with an assortment of condiments: Whipped cream, lemon curd, whipped butter, and jam, but only a teaspoon of each was offered for such a massive scone, and there certainly was not enough platted for two people to share. By the way, real Clotted Cream, or Devonshire cream is not available, instead, we were provided with a thin, watery whipped cream that quickly melted into a puddle
Lastly, we sampled the pea salad, which again was terrible. This reminded me of the seven layer salad that my mother used to make long ago at family gatherings.
On a positive note, I will say that the establishment is beautifully decorated, and I adored the theme of English meets Orient. The decor, wallpaper, and furnishings were artfully chosen and displayed; Its obvious a lot of attention and money went into the decor. I only wish they had just put as much effort into the food also.
Not returning.

We came this morning as my cousin is getting married and planned to ask my daughters to be her flower girls. She had
bought pre-packaged/wrapped cookies that said “will you be my flower girl“ on them. A blonde server walked by us first with a look of disdain on her face as we waited in line to place our breakfast/tea order. She came back and asked us if we had cookies and told us we could not have “outside food” as if we had brought  a package of Oreos or McDonald’s into the restaurant. We clearly planned to order food  there and the cookies were wrapped in a clear box as a parting gift for my children. Her tone was rude and unwelcoming so we left. I have worked in the food industry many years and while the lady may have thought she was doing her job, there could have been a kinder approach. It honestly just felt like she wanted to get rid of us as we had 7 people. It wasn’t like we planned to sit and take up a whole table while we munched on our cookies. Also if you are going to be that peculiar, you might want to work on your 93 sanitation score. I do want to add that the gentleman/host up front was very kind but it went sour fast.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello Cristen! I am disappointed to hear that you were not able to have the experience that you expected at A Cause for Tea. From reading your review, I can see that it was a deeply disappointing and frustrating experience for you to discover that your plans for a very special occasion would need to be modified in order to align with our organization’s guidelines and mission. Disappointed and frustrated guests is not our team’s desire. Our team’s and organization’s primary objective is the empowerment of women and children living in desperate situations. One of the many ways that we seek to accomplish this objective is the creation of positive customer experiences. If you would like to further discuss this situation with us, we would value the conversation. Congratulations to your cousin and family on the upcoming celebration of marriage.
